Nagsangit   dagiti  lallakay kada   babbaket
n-ag-sangit dagiti  lallakay kada   babbaket
PF-I-cry    CORE.PL old.men  and.PL old.women
'the old men and women (husbands and wives) cried'

# Week 4
# Ken is able to have either singular or plural on either side.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {coordination agreement}
Nagsangit   dagiti  lallakay ken   babbaket
n-ag-sangit dagiti  lallakay ken   babbaket
PF-I-cry    CORE.PL old.men  and   old.women
'the old men and women (husbands and wives) cried'

# Week 4
# Ken has a plural form, kada, used to coordinate plural nouns only.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {coordination agreement}
Nagsangit    ti      lalaki kada   ti      babai
n-ag-sangit  ti      lalaki kada   ti      babai
 PF-I-cry    CORE.SG boy    and.PL CORE.SG girl
'the boy and the girl cried'


