# Week 4
# A properly formed 'what' question in which the interrogative
# is followed by 'ti' and a verb with an ergative enclitic pronoun:
Source: a:430
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wh}
Ania ti      ginatangmo
ania ti      gatang-{in}=mo
what CORE.SG buy-{PF.T}=ERG.2SG
'What did you buy?'

# Week 4
# Another 'what' question following the same pattern, but with the
# ergative enclitic on a glossed adjective.
Source: a:431
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wh}
Ania ti      dakesmo
ania ti      dakes=mo
what CORE.SG bad=ERG.2SG
'What's wrong with you?'

# Week 4
# An incorrectly formed question where 'ti' is omitted before an encliticized word.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {wh}
Ania ginatangmo
ania gatang-{in}=mo
what buy-{PF.T}=ERG.2SG
'What did you buy?'

# Week 4
# A 'who' question formed similarly to the above questions.
Source: a:435
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wh}
Sino ti      amam?
sino ti	    ama=mo
who  CORE.SG father=ERG.2SG
'Who is your father?'

# Week 4
# A 'who' question with absolutive enclitic pronoun on the verb.
